import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    restaurant_counts = data['key'].value_counts()
    restaurant_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xlabel('Restaurant Types')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of restaurant types in the U-District?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    counts = data['lat'].value_counts()
    avg_latitude = data['lat'].mean()
    
    plt.scatter(counts.index, counts.values)
    plt.axvline(avg_latitude, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Latitude: {avg_latitude:.2f}')
    
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    plt.ylabel('Restaurant Count')
    plt.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the average latitude of restaurants in the U-District?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
